## Conversation
PR1: page-cache leak fix. Evolved through review:
1. v1: per-instance OrderedDict LRU.
2. Review comment "what if a helper func that used lru_cache?" -> switched to a
   module-level _make_page_fetcher returning an lru_cache-wrapped closure
   (demo + Codex; user chose it; Codex preferred OrderedDict but user overrode).
3. Review comment "I wonder if this should be a staticmethod" + "yes" -> moved
   _make_page_fetcher into PaginatedIterator as a @staticmethod; call site is
   self._make_page_fetcher(...).

## Actions
- @staticmethod _make_page_fetcher(fetch_func, page_size, max_cached_pages)
  returns @lru_cache(maxsize=...) closure over fetch_func+page_size only.
- Verified staticmethod + class-TypeVar typing with `uvx mypy --strict` on
  .context/staticmethod_check.py (both free-func and staticmethod forms green).
- ruff clean; 5 unit tests pass incl. weakref release-after-del (leak guard).

