## Hints for Future Agents
- INVARIANT: the cache closure must not capture the iterator. @staticmethod
  enforces no-self by construction, but if anyone converts it to a regular
  method to read self.page_size etc., the leak returns and ruff B019 will NOT
  flag it (decorator is on the nested fetch_page, not a method). Keep the
  weakref release test as the guardrail.
- __init__ calls self._make_page_fetcher before its definition in the class
  body -- fine, method lookup is at call time.

## Codebase Discoveries
- PaginatedIterator is fully self-contained: no subclasses; nothing outside
  paginated_iterator.py touches _fetch_page/_make_page_fetcher/fetch_func; sole
  construction site is call.py:417. FetchFunc contract unchanged, so no
  fetch_func implementation needed changes.

